---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting"
  description="Consulting and workshops on responsible AI use in work, communication, decisions and team processes."
>
  <div class="lovable-page">
    <header class="lovable-page-hero consulting-hero">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="consulting-hero-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Consulting</p>
            <h1>Consulting</h1>
            <p class="lede">
              I help people and teams work with AI more deliberately: ask better
              questions, verify outputs, design processes and keep responsibility
              for decisions with humans.
            </p>
          </div>
          <aside class="consulting-side-note">
            <p class="small-label">Approach</p>
            <p>
              I do not start with a tool or a list of prompts. First we need to see
              where AI enters the work, what it can genuinely support and where it
              creates false certainty, overreliance or blurred responsibility.
            </p>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="lovable-section" aria-labelledby="audience-title">
      <div class="lovable-container outcome-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Who it is for</p>
          <h2 id="audience-title">For people and teams that want to use AI more carefully</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="outcome-list">
          <li>creators, editors and communication teams working with text, image or narrative</li>
          <li>companies and teams already using AI without shared verification rules</li>
          <li>people designing processes, content, decisions and communication with AI support</li>
          <li>organizations building AI literacy without hype or prompt tricks</li>
          <li>leaders who want to understand the risks of overreliance on models</li>
          <li>teams that need to connect human judgment with model outputs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section tinted-section" aria-labelledby="services-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="lovable-section-header">
          <h2 id="services-title">What I help with</h2>
          <p>
            I work with real tasks and examples from the process. The aim is for AI
            to support thinking, communication and decisions without replacing human
            judgment.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="lovable-service-list">
          <li>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>AI work audit</h3>
            <p>I map where a team already uses AI, what works, what is unclear and where verification is missing.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Responsible workflows</h3>
            <p>I help define what a model can prepare, what needs checking and where the decision stays with a person.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>AI literacy workshops</h3>
            <p>I build shared language around context, sources, model output, trust, limits and responsibility.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Communication and decisions</h3>
            <p>I help teams see how AI changes writing, information assessment, recommendations and team conversation.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>05</span>
            <h3>Team AI principles</h3>
            <p>I help clarify rules for data, sources, citation, quality control and responsibility for the result.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>06</span>
            <h3>Risk analysis</h3>
            <p>I identify places where overreliance, false certainty, missing sources or delegated decisions can appear.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section" aria-labelledby="situations-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Signals</p>
          <h2 id="situations-title">When it makes sense to talk</h2>
        </div>
        <ol class="lovable-numbered-list">
          <li>A team uses AI, but has no shared way to verify outputs.</li>
          <li>AI speeds up work, but the line between support and risk is unclear.</li>
          <li>People copy model answers without checking sources, assumptions and gaps.</li>
          <li>Decisions start to rely on fluent answers rather than the underlying material.</li>
          <li>AI-assisted communication becomes faster, but less accountable.</li>
          <li>You want a workflow that strengthens people instead of replacing them.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section tinted-section process-section" aria-labelledby="process-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Working method</p>
          <h2 id="process-title">How I work</h2>
          <p>
            Consulting should begin with context, not a ready-made formula. I work
            with concrete tasks, decisions and risk points.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="process-line process-line-detailed" aria-label="Consulting working method">
          <li><small>01</small><strong>Context</strong><span>where AI appears in the work and what it should actually support</span></li>
          <li><small>02</small><strong>Goals and limits</strong><span>team needs, risks, data and realistic boundaries for AI use</span></li>
          <li><small>03</small><strong>Process examples</strong><span>concrete tasks, texts, decisions or information flows</span></li>
          <li><small>04</small><strong>Principles and practice</strong><span>rules, control questions and ways to verify model outputs</span></li>
          <li><small>05</small><strong>Responsibility</strong><span>the model may support the work, but decisions and consequences stay with people</span></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section outcome-section" aria-labelledby="boundaries-title">
      <div class="lovable-container outcome-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Boundaries</p>
          <h2 id="boundaries-title">What I do not do</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="outcome-list">
          <li>I do not diagnose people from messages, notes or workplace behavior</li>
          <li>I do not use AI for manipulation, pressure or guessing hidden intentions</li>
          <li>I do not promise that a model will be right or solve the problem for the team</li>
          <li>I do not sell ready-made "magic prompts" as a substitute for thinking</li>
          <li>I do not remove responsibility from a person, leader or organization</li>
          <li>I do not replace legal, medical, psychological or HR support where a specialist is needed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <p class="disclaimer-line">
          This is not technical deployment, therapy, diagnosis, legal advice or a promise of business outcomes.
        </p>
        <div class="consulting-actions">
          <a class="hero-button hero-button-primary" href="/contact/"><span aria-hidden="true"></span>Ask about consulting</a>
          <a class="hero-button hero-button-secondary" href="/concepts/">Read concepts</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
